case.name: Morton, in the matter of Robert William Morton (in hiscapacity as liquidator of Incentive Dynamics Pty Ltd) [2006] FCA 229 (7 March 2006)

citances.sentence: In Chen v MIMIA [2006] FCA 229 Lander J at [111], considering the operation of section 137L stated that "any circumstances that are exceptional, in the sense that they are unusual and not of the applicant's own making, but beyond the applicant's control, may provide a reason for the Minister revoking the cancellation".
